# Core Next.js Workflow

- Treat this project as **Next.js 16**; do not assume older Next.js behavior.
- Before implementing framework-specific behavior, check relevant docs in `node_modules/next/dist/docs/`.
- Prefer minimal, targeted edits over broad refactors.
- Preserve existing user changes and avoid destructive git commands.

## Validation Checklist

- Run the smallest relevant verification step after edits (lint, typecheck, or focused build step).
- If verification cannot run, explicitly state what was not verified and why.
- Keep `.gitignore` aligned with generated artifacts when adding new tools.

## Code Style

- Follow existing project patterns in `src/` for naming and file organization.
- Add brief comments only where logic is non-obvious.
